# Index Schema

The knowledge index is a pre-built inverted index mapping tokens to source-section pairs.

## Structure

```json
{
  "version": 1,
  "built": "2026-07-02T12:00:00Z",
  "sources": {
    "forward/deploy.md": {
      "title": "Deployment Guide",
      "type": "forward",
      "bytes": 4500,
      "sections": {
        "## Prerequisites": {
          "preview": "你需要安装 Python 3.9+ 和 Docker。",
          "token_count": 42
        },
        "## Steps": {
          "preview": "1. 构建 Docker 镜像\n2. 推送到镜像仓库...",
          "token_count": 156
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "inverted": {
    "deploy": [
      {"source": "forward/deploy.md", "section": "## Steps", "tf": 0.042},
      {"source": "capsule/errors.md", "section": "## Connection Refused", "tf": 0.018}
    ],
    "docker": [
      {"source": "forward/deploy.md", "section": "## Prerequisites", "tf": 0.071}
    ]
  },
  "source_mtimes": {
    "forward/deploy.md": 1719900000.0
  }
}
```

## Browser Search Algorithm

```
search(query, index, max_chunks=5):
    tokens = tokenize(query)
    scores = {}  # source#section -> cumulative score
    
    for token in tokens:
        if token in index.inverted:
            for entry in index.inverted[token]:
                key = f"{entry.source}#{entry.section}"
                scores[key] = scores.get(key, 0) + entry.tf
    
    ranked = sorted(scores.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
    return ranked[:max_chunks]
```

## Fields

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `version` | int | Schema version |
| `built` | ISO8601 | Index build timestamp |
| `sources` | object | File metadata keyed by relative path |
| `sources[key].title` | string | Document title (from # header) |
| `sources[key].type` | string | Knowledge type: forward/reverse/capsule |
| `sources[key].bytes` | int | File size in bytes |
| `sources[key].sections` | object | Sections keyed by ## header name |
| `sources[key].sections[].preview` | string | First 200 chars of section content |
| `sources[key].sections[].token_count` | int | Number of tokens in section |
| `inverted` | object | Token → [{source, section, tf}] |
| `inverted[token][].source` | string | Relative file path |
| `inverted[token][].section` | string | Section header |
| `inverted[token][].tf` | float | Term frequency in section |
| `source_mtimes` | object | File modification timestamps for change detection |
